properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 17 at 1:31PM CST until January 17 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Aberdeen SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of up to one inch,
with storm total accumulations of 1 to 3 inches. Winds gusting
as high as 50 mph.

* WHERE...Sully and Hughes Counties.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Patchy to areas of
blowing snow could significantly reduce visibility. The
hazardous conditions could impact the evening commute. Gusty
winds could bring down tree branches.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
